the body’s direct response to some external situation. An emotion, on the other hand, is the body’s response to thought. Indirectly, an emotion can also be a response to an actual situation or event, but it will be a response to the event seen through the filter of a mental interpretation, the future of thought, that is to say, through the mental concepts of good and bad, like and dislike, me and mine.', 378, 0), (237064, 'Whatever neutrality is, it is not very useful to anybody, and time is running out. If we do not do useful things whenever it is possible or necessary to do them, we shall soon be totally departed from the human scene, and forgotten, or remembered only for having disappeared. Armenians are too vital to be permitted to throw themselves away in neutrality, comfort, well-being, satisfaction, and so on and so forth.', 2919, 0), (237065, 'Hope lies in action', 591, 0), (237066, 'Initiative without action is the same as having the mind to acknowledge a problem, but not having the heart to see it through.', 2678, 0), (237067, 'Touch of Ability with Action can never be lost in the journey of life.', 23468, 0), (237068, '...Defeat appears to me preferable to total Inaction.', 4179, 0), (237069, 'God has written us a book, and now we have the opportunity to respond with our words and actions.', 14846, 0), (237070, 'Happiness is the fragrance, not the fruit of an action.', 2586, 0), (237071, 'Not the action, but the expectation creates results.', 2586, 0), (237072, 'Are you waiting for the approval of someone else before you make your big move? If you are, chances are they’ve already made it.', 5190, 0), (237073, 'We kept our heads down and did our jobs. We controlled the only thing we could, which was the show. We did the thing. Because remember, the talking about the thing isn''t the thing. The doing of the thing is the thing.', 1498, 0), (237074, 'How the Hell is it we go to pick up Jenna Jameson and end up with the fucking chick from those Kill Bill movie