INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (237101, 'The test of our knowledge is not what we know, but what we can do.', 884, 0), (237102, 'Action is the means through which the intangible becomes tangible.', 5302, 0), (237103, 'Hard work is great. It buys you more tickets to the luck lottery.', 41688, 0), (237104, 'The twins stopped and stared in surprise at the two vampires guarding a door on their right. The vampires returned their look of surprise."What are you doing here?" One of the vampires hissed."We''re looking for Taco Bell." Luther said cheerfully as he and Tyrone reached behind their backs."Left or right, Tyrone?""I''ll take the one on the left." Tyrone replied.', 41689, 0), (237105, 'It is injustice to determine the brutality of an action because of the victim or the criminal.', 4238, 0), (237106, 'But fear of making mistakes can itself become a huge mistake, one that prevents you from living, for life is risky and anything less is already a loss.', 797, 0), (237107, 'I rolled my eyes. To Jack I said, "Don''t mind him, he''s just mad no one likes him."Jonas clenched his jaw.', 33525, 0), (237108, 'The time you absolutely have to get off your ass and act is when action seems futile', 884, 0), (237109, 'Being a philosopher requires a lot of thinking and no action. Being a model requires a lot of action and no thinking.', 4616, 0), (237110, 'Although, in my defense, a nonblinking eye rape was rarely the kind of thing you just eased into.', 33525, 0), (237111, 'The surgical resident interested in learning trauma will bypass a residency at a quiet community hospital for a residency at a fast-paced Level 1 trauma center treating a high volume of trauma patients. A Level 1 trauma center residency is far more rigorous—and not particularly glamorous—but the intensive culture of a dedicated trauma center will cultivate the decisive judgment and action required of a surgeon specializing in trauma. By choice or by chance, we must actively test our limits to know our capabilities.', 38090, 0), (237112, 'You will find your purpose revealed in every single action, once you realize that — you — are your purpose.', 7223, 0), (237113, 'Everyday, in our quest to grab the new, the trendy, the coolest stuff, we forget to use the old and our daily lives become stuck in the vicious cycle, chasing after stuff without working the old. Today, pause, slow down, take time, revisit those lessons, materials and take the necessary baby-steps. It pays. Go, make it happen!', 5532, 0), (237114, 'Napoleon the greatest of the conquerors, is a sufficient proof that great men of action are criminals, and, therefore not geniuses. One can understand him by thinking of the tremendous intensity with which he tried to escape from himself.', 13564, 0), (237115, 'Studying the rule of law won''t make a great litigator. It is the act of trying cases in real courtrooms with real plaintiffs and defendants and judges and juries, week after week and year after year that develops lawyers into top trial attorneys.', 38090, 0), (237116, 'Studying the rule of law won''t make a great litigator. It is the act of trying cases in real courtrooms with real plaintiffs and defendants and judges and juries, week after week and year after year that develops lawyers into top trial attorneys. ― Marian Deegan', 38090, 0), (237117, 'Love is a lens of an observer. Love is an attitude with action.', 7223, 0), (237118, 'My fangs extended then, automatically, like her voice were a fang charmer, and I followed impulsively, thinking about blood.', 41690, 0), (237119, 'Hurrying back into the rouge lighting in sheer terror, Amelia ran without another word, escaping into the shadows of the dungeon, and she shrieked for salvation that never came.', 41690, 0), (237120, 'All human happiness or misery takes the form of action', 41691, 0), (237121, 'Like two lost souls, we fall asleep in each other''s arms, hoping to find ourselves once again.', 6839, 0), (237122, 'सक्ताः कर्मण्