INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (237451, 'A poem does not radiate from the name, but the name emanates from the poem.', 2610, 0), (237452, 'The name does not deserve the poem, but the poem deserves the name.', 2610, 0), (237453, 'In a real poem a sound does not swallow a letter, but a letter swallows a sound.', 2610, 0), (237454, 'Death lurks in the shadows, just out of view. Now and then I see his reaching hand, uncertain of the blurry image that passes before my eyes, but conscious of the crippling influence of his touch. Some say Death rears an ugly head, so hideous a view the beholder can scarcely gasp their last breath. Others call him beautiful, a sweet relief to look upon. But these are rumors babbled by the unknowing. For Death is like the gorgon, Medusa, who when perceived, turns the body to stone. Those who know Death take the knowledge of his shadowed face with them to wherever it is he leads our dearly departed by the hand. All who are left behind must wait their turn to glance into the eyes of the one who will close our mouths forever.', 1456, 0), (237455, 'Rash is he who at unknown doors relies on his good luck.', 41746, 0), (237456, 'What if dragons breathed bubbles and purred when they cuddled and giggled at chivalrous knights for their troubles?What if dragons felt soft, having scales made of cloth,and they moved rather slow like a brown-throated sloth?What if dragons were shyand did easily crywhen confronted by characters callous and sly?What if dragons did goodbut were misunderstoodso men mercilessly slew the beasts right where they stood?What if dragons aren’t missedbecause there is no listof extinct types of quarry that now don’t exist?', 1456, 0), (237457, 'Sipping teawith gleebeneath a gooseberry tree.I wish Alice were here.Oh, my dear,do not fear,she will be.', 1456, 0), (237458, 'Does poem also walk the valleys seeking tongues from dandelions?', 10412, 0), (237459, 'What is poetry? Only the poetry can answer this!',